t: To the chief Musician, A Psalm of David, to bring to remembrance.
Make*p haste, O God, to deliver me; make haste to help me, O Lord.*s
Let*p them be ashamed and confounded that seek after my soul: let them be turned backward, and put to confusion, that desire my hurt.
Let*p them be turned back for a reward of their shame that say, Aha, aha.
Let*p all those that seek thee rejoice and be glad in thee: and let such as love thy salvation say continually, Let God be magnified.
But*p I am poor and needy: make haste unto me, O God: thou art my help and my deliverer; O Lord,*s make no tarrying.
